{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"159a1bbd-8a77-4b0f-b331-22458b09b7ca","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n\n// For theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest(int value) { }\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\nKey differences:\n- **MSTest & NUnit** both use `[Ignore(\"reason\")]`\n- **xUnit** uses a `Skip` property on `[Fact]`/`[Theory]`\n- **TUnit** uses `[Skip(\"reason\")]`\n\nAll four report the reason in test results so you can track why tests were skipped.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c70225f4-fe23-4822-a0b4-6bd13ac00d2b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":311,"requestId":"A029:903FB:18AE122:1BF8064:69FE8A1E"},"id":"288aae65-b842-4dcd-bdb0-36b7479b4527","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:13:14.398Z","parentId":"c8538bab-e8ee-47c3-90bc-46ac1a4dc481"}
